data.description: This 4 bedroom, 3.5 bath and 3 car garage home has wonderful space for your family. The large kitchen with massive island overlooks the breakfast nook, the den with additional fireplace and the family room. The family room has a floor to ceiling stone fireplace with vaulted ceilings. The primary bedroom is tucked away on the first floor and is a great size. The primary bathroom has dual vanities, separate shower and tub and wonderful walk-in closets. The laundry room is massive with a built-in mud bench, space for additional freezer or fridge and sink. The office is up the stairs and is a wonderful size. Upstairs you have 3 secondary bedrooms a large game room and media room. Storage in this home is not lacking. Don't miss the door inside the coat closet that leads to storage under the stairs. Home has solar panels that help reduce the electric bill. Solar panels will remain on the home. Shed in the backyard can stay if buyers would like.
